rComments: She's funny and interesting, and I actually did like that she handwrites her notes, but her tests are quite frustrating. The way she words questions makes it difficult to know what, exactly, she might be looking for -- and digression or providing more information, beyond that which was offered directly given in class, was frowned upon.

She teaches at The University of Arizona. She's not the best. Her notes are all written on paper and projected via overhead. Ecology isn't hard but she makes it difficult. Many of the questions on her exams are worded poorly and she will even say so herself in retrospect. If you try to argue points back she will side with the TA's every time.

She is a very nice person with a strong interest in ecology. While I don't like her style of writing on the projector while lecturing, it means she goes slowly and is clear and concise. This class was insanely easy if you show up. You have to because she doesn't post anything online, but the study guides are literally the exam. Easy A.

She teaches at the University of Arizona now and she was pretty cool. She seemed to like the subject, but was very overexcited most of the time. Her tests questions can be confusing, but she extra credit on every test, and he quizzes are so easy you do not have to know anything about ecology to do well since only one answer makes sense.
she a meany sometimes. Doesn't give a straight answer but rathers asks you a question and leaves it at that.
